            "type": "paragraph",
            "content": "Duct sizing follows Manual D methodology established by the Air Conditioning Contractors of America (ACCA). This engineering approach calculates exact duct sizes based on required CFM (cubic feet per minute) airflow to each room determined by Manual J load calculations, total available static pressure budget from your HVAC equipment (typically 0.5 inches for residential), allowable friction rate (pressure drop per 100 feet of duct), typically 0.06-0.08 inches, duct routing distance and configuration including straight runs, turns, and fittings, and desired air velocity to prevent noise—typically 600-900 feet per minute for residential. The calculations determine optimal duct diameters (for round duct) or dimensions (for rectangular) that deliver required airflow without exceeding pressure limits or creating noise."
