            "type": "paragraph",
            "content": "Proper duct design requires balanced supply and return airflow. Many Tucson homes have adequate supply ducts but severely undersized returns—often just one small grille for the entire house. Inadequate return capacity creates negative pressure that pulls unconditioned air into your home through leaks, forces your system to work harder moving air against high resistance, creates whistling, whooshing sounds at return grilles, and prevents proper air circulation and comfort. We design return duct systems with total free area (grille size) of at least 2 square inches per CFM of system capacity, multiple return grilles strategically located for optimal air circulation, and properly sized return ducts connecting grilles to air handler. This balanced approach eliminates pressure problems and maximizes efficiency."
